      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ",) the person whom he trusted with his secrets, and whose conversation was most pleasant and acceptable to him. Observe, a cunning man was his counsellor: but an honest man was his friend. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "After Ahithophel — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "After his death, these were his chief counsellors. Much of the wisdom of princes is seen in the choice of their ministry. It appears that those whom David made choice of to attend upon and advise him, were such as were peculiarly eminent for wisdom and integrity. But though he had these trusty counsellors about him, he preferred his Bible before them all, making the Lord’s ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "testimonies his delight and his counsellors, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Psalm 119:24",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
